THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 118A of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
2 section to read as follows:
3 1. A landlord of a covered premises [comprising more than 100 dwelling
4 units attached to a single parcel of property] shall establish:
5 (a) A policy requiring an applicant for employment with the landlord to
6 undergo a criminal background check as a condition of employment if the
7 position for which the applicant is applying entails access to any dwelling unit
8 key; and
9 (b) Written policies and procedures regarding the:
10 (1) Storage, issuance, return and security of dwelling unit keys; and
11 (2) If applicable, the usage and deactivation of dwelling unit keys.
12 2. A landlord of a covered premises shall maintain on the premises a log
13 that accounts for the issuance and return of each dwelling unit key and the
14 written policies and procedures established pursuant to paragraph (b) of
15 subsection 1.
16 3. In addition to any other remedies, if a landlord of a covered premises
17 violates this section, a person aggrieved by the violation or a district attorney may
18 bring a civil action in a court of competent jurisdiction against the landlord to
19 seek any or all of the following relief:
20 (a) Declaratory and injunctive relief.
21 (b) Actual damages.
22 (c) Reasonable attorney’s fees and costs.
23 (d) Any other legal or equitable relief that the court deems appropriate.
24 4. As used in this section:
25 (a) “Covered premises” means:
26 (1) In a county whose population is 100,000 or more, a premises
27 comprising more than 50 dwelling units attached to a single parcel of property;
28 or
29 (2) In a county whose population is less than 100,000, a premises
30 comprising more than 10 dwelling units attached to a single parcel of property.
31 (b) “Dwelling unit key” means any physical or electronic mechanism used to
32 gain access to a dwelling unit, including, without limitation, a combination or
33 access code.
34 [(b)] (c) “Financial institution” means any bank, savings and loan
35 association, savings bank, thrift company, credit union or financial institution
36 that is licensed, registered or otherwise authorized to do business in this State.
37 [(c)] (d) “Landlord” [means a landlord of a premises comprising more than
38 100 dwelling units attached to a single parcel of property. The term] does not
39 include a financial institution, real estate broker, real estate broker-salesperson
40 or real estate salesperson.
41 [(d)] (e) “Real estate broker” has the meaning ascribed to it in NRS 645.030.
42 [(e)] (f) “Real estate broker-salesperson” has the meaning ascribed to it in
43 NRS 645.035.
44 [(f)] (g) “Real estate salesperson” has the meaning ascribed to it in NRS
45 645.040.

